        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-26T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-26T22:00:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/10–2748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-27T11:00:00+08:00">October 27, 1948—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 27—3:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2011. Regret we did not make ourselves clear in fourth paragraph our 1985,
                    October 24 (Deptel 1488, October 26). Chief JUSMAG has previously on personal
                    and confidential basis recommended Generalissimo withdrawal forces Mukden with
                    instructions fight their way intramural China and we merely took advantage
                    Generalissimo’s plea to have chief JUSMAG renew his recommendations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
